metadata/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpcore/index.json:65:    "description" : "Apache HttpCore provides low-level components for building HTTP clients and servers with blocking I/O. It implements core HTTP message parsing, transport, and connection management primitives used by higher-level HttpComponents libraries.",
metadata/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpcore/index.json:79:    "description" : "Apache HttpCore provides low-level components for building HTTP clients and servers with classic blocking I/O. It implements core HTTP message parsing, transport, and connection management primitives used by higher-level HttpComponents libraries.",
metadata/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpcore/index.json:93:    "description" : "Apache HttpCore provides the low-level components for building HTTP clients and servers with blocking I/O. It implements core HTTP message parsing, transport, and connection management primitives used by higher-level HttpComponents libraries.",
metadata/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpcore/index.json:107:    "description" : "Apache HttpCore provides low-level components for building HTTP clients and servers with blocking I/O. It implements core HTTP message parsing, transport, and connection management primitives used by higher-level HttpComponents libraries.",
metadata/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpcore/index.json:121:    "description" : "Apache HttpCore provides low-level components for building HTTP clients and servers with blocking I/O. It implements core HTTP message parsing, transport, and connection management primitives used by higher-level HttpComponents libraries.",
metadata/io.github.resilience4j/resilience4j-reactor/index.json:9:    "description" : "Resilience4j Reactor integrates Resilience4j's fault-tolerance primitives with Project Reactor Flux and Mono pipelines. It provides Reactor operators and adapters for applying circuit breakers, rate limiters, bulkheads, retries, time limiters, and Micrometer timers around reactive streams.",
metadata/com.github.virtuald/curvesapi/index.json:9:    "description" : "curvesapi provides Java implementations of mathematical curves defined over control points. It supports Bezier, B-Spline, Cardinal Spline, Catmull-Rom Spline, Lagrange, Natural Cubic Spline, and NURBS curve types.",
metadata/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpmime/index.json:21:    "description" : "Apache HttpMime is the MIME multipart entity module for Apache HttpComponents HttpClient. It provides support for building and handling MIME multipart encoded HTTP entities, such as form-data uploads, used by HttpClient applications.",
metadata/io.github.resilience4j/resilience4j-circuitbreaker/index.json:9:    "description" : "Resilience4j CircuitBreaker provides a lightweight Java implementation of the circuit breaker pattern for guarding calls to unreliable dependencies. It tracks call outcomes and latency, transitions between closed, open, and half-open states, and can be configured with failure-rate, slow-call, wait-duration, and permitted-call thresholds.",
metadata/com.beust/jcommander/index.json:9:    "description" : "JCommander is an annotation-based command-line parsing framework for Java applications. It maps command-line arguments onto Java objects, supports typed converters and validators, and helps generate usage output for command-line tools.",
metadata/com.beust/jcommander/index.json:23:    "description" : "JCommander is an annotation-based command-line parsing framework for Java applications. It maps command-line arguments onto Java objects, supports typed converters and validators, and helps generate usage output for command-line tools.",
metadata/com.beust/jcommander/index.json:37:    "description" : "JCommander is an annotation-based command-line parsing framework for Java applications. It maps command-line arguments onto Java objects, supports typed converters and validators, and helps generate usage output for command-line tools.",
metadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-starter/index.json:3:    "not-for-native-image": true,
metadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-configuration-processor/index.json:9:    "description" : "Spring Boot Configuration Processor is a compile-time Java annotation processor that generates configuration metadata from Spring Boot configuration property classes. The generated metadata helps IDEs and other tools provide contextual documentation, validation hints, and property completion for Spring Boot application configuration.",
metadata/org.apache.kerby/kerby-util/index.json:9:    "description" : "Kerby Util provides common utility classes for Apache Kerby, including Base64, hex, byte and line I/O, network address parsing, public-key derivation, and OS or system helpers. It is designed as a lightweight shared utility module without third-party dependencies for Kerby components.",
metadata/org.jooq/jooq/index.json:10:    "description" : "jOOQ is a Java library for building and executing type-safe SQL against relational databases. It models SQL as a fluent DSL and can generate Java classes from database schemas to improve query safety and developer ergonomics.",
metadata/org.jooq/jooq/index.json:41:    "description" : "jOOQ is a Java library for building and executing type-safe SQL against relational databases. It models SQL as a fluent DSL and can generate Java classes from database schemas to improve query safety and developer ergonomics.",
metadata/org.jooq/jooq/index.json:117:    "description" : "jOOQ is a Java library for building and executing type-safe SQL against relational databases. It models SQL as a fluent DSL and can generate Java classes from database schemas to improve query safety and developer ergonomics.",
metadata/org.apache.kerby/kerby-pkix/index.json:9:    "description" : "Kerby PKIX provides Java ASN.1 model classes and helpers for PKI structures such as X.509 certificates, attribute certificates, CRLs, X.500 names, and CMS content. It is part of Apache Kerby and supplies certificate and message type definitions plus basic PKI utility hooks built on Kerby's ASN.1 and utility modules.",
metadata/io.github.resilience4j/resilience4j-micrometer/index.json:9:    "description" : "Resilience4j Micrometer integrates Resilience4j's bulkhead, circuit breaker, rate limiter, retry, time limiter, and timer metrics with Micrometer. It lets JVM applications publish resilience and fault-tolerance metrics through Micrometer registries for monitoring systems.",
metadata/com.github.pureconfig/pureconfig-generic-base_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "PureConfig is a Scala library for loading HOCON, JSON, and Java properties configuration into typed Scala data structures. The pureconfig-generic-base module provides shared generic derivation support, including product and coproduct hints used to customize case class and sealed trait mapping.",
metadata/com.github.pureconfig/pureconfig-generic-base_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.typelevel/cats-core_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "cats-core_3 provides Cats' core abstractions and data types for functional programming in Scala, including type classes such as Functor, Monad, Monoid, and Traverse. It supplies syntax, instances, and utilities that let Scala 3 applications compose effectful and generic code without depending on a specific effect runtime.",
metadata/org.typelevel/cats-core_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.apache.kerby/kerby-asn1/index.json:9:    "description" : "Apache Kerby ASN.1 provides Java classes for encoding, decoding, parsing, and dumping ASN.1 data structures. It includes primitive and constructed ASN.1 types plus BER, DER, and CER support used by Kerby and other protocol or security code.",
metadata/io.github.resilience4j/resilience4j-core/index.json:9:    "description" : "Resilience4j Core provides shared functional utilities, registries, event processing, interval functions, predicates, and metrics support used by Resilience4j fault-tolerance modules. It forms the common foundation for decorating Java functional interfaces and asynchronous calls with resilience patterns such as circuit breakers, retries, rate limiters, bulkheads, and time limiters.",
metadata/com.github.pureconfig/pureconfig-core_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "PureConfig Core is a Scala library for loading Typesafe Config, HOCON, JSON, and Java properties configuration into typed Scala data structures. It provides the core readers, writers, cursors, naming conventions, and derivation support used to map configuration values to case classes, sealed traits, collections, options, and custom types.",
metadata/com.github.pureconfig/pureconfig-core_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.typelevel/twiddles-core_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "Twiddles provides twiddle lists for incrementally composing values of different types and converting them to shape-compatible case classes. The core module offers syntax and abstractions for building protocol-like structures such as decoders, encoders, and codecs using Cats invariant semigroupal and invariant type classes.",
metadata/org.typelevel/twiddles-core_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.apache.kerby/kerby-config/index.json:9:    "description" : "Kerby Config is Apache Kerby's configuration library, providing a unified API for loading and accessing configuration data. It supports common formats such as XML, JSON, INI, properties, and map-based configuration sources.",
metadata/io.github.resilience4j/resilience4j-retry/index.json:9:    "description" : "Resilience4j Retry provides a lightweight Java fault-tolerance component for retrying failed calls with configurable attempts, wait intervals, and exception or result predicates. The module exposes core retry APIs, registries, events, and decorators that can wrap synchronous, asynchronous, and functional-style JVM code.",
metadata/org.apache.kerby/kerb-core/index.json:9:    "description" : "Apache Kerby is a Java Kerberos implementation that provides client, KDC, PKI, OTP, and token authentication facilities for Kerberos-based systems. The kerb-core module contains the core Kerberos protocol types, codecs, constants, and provider abstractions used by the broader Kerby stack.",
metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "Cats Effect is a high-performance, asynchronous runtime and effect system for building purely functional Scala applications. It provides the IO data type, resource-safety tools, concurrency primitives, and type classes for describing and controlling side effects.",
metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/index.json:117:    "description" : "Cats Effect is a high-performance, asynchronous, and composable framework for building real-world Scala applications in a purely functional style. It provides the IO data type, resource-safety tools, concurrency primitives, and type classes for describing and controlling side effects.",
metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/index.json:118:    "language" : {
metadata/com.github.pureconfig/pureconfig-generic-scala3_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "pureconfig-generic-scala3 provides Scala 3 generic derivation support for PureConfig, deriving ConfigReader and ConfigWriter instances for case classes, enums, sealed families, and value classes. It lets Scala 3 applications load Typesafe Config/HOCON, JSON, or Java properties into strongly typed Scala models with less boilerplate while honoring PureConfig product and coproduct hints.",
metadata/com.github.pureconfig/pureconfig-generic-scala3_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
