metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-api/index.json:8:    "description" : "JJWT provides APIs for creating, parsing, and verifying JSON Web Tokens and JSON Web Keys in Java and Android applications. The `jjwt-api` artifact exposes the library's public interfaces, fluent builders, and supporting types for JOSE-compliant JWT processing.",
metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-api/index.json:23:    "description" : "JJWT provides APIs for creating, parsing, and verifying JSON Web Tokens and JSON Web Keys in Java and Android applications. The `jjwt-api` artifact exposes the library's stable public interfaces and fluent builders for JOSE-compliant JWT processing.",
metadata/com.google.auto.service/auto-service/index.json:9:    "description" : "AutoService is a Java annotation processor that generates java.util.ServiceLoader provider-configuration files for classes annotated with @AutoService. It helps service-provider implementations stay correctly registered by generating META-INF/services metadata during compilation instead of requiring developers to maintain those files by hand.",
metadata/org.jline/jline-console/index.json:9:    "description" : "JLine Console provides higher-level console framework APIs for building interactive command-line applications on top of JLine. It includes command registry, console engine, system registry, printer, widget, and built-in command support for managing command execution, scripting, completion, and terminal output.",
metadata/org.jline/jline-console/index.json:56:    "description" : "JLine Console provides higher-level console framework APIs for building interactive command-line applications on top of JLine. It includes command registry, console engine, system registry, printer, widget, and built-in command support for managing command execution, scripting, completion, and terminal output.",
metadata/com.google.auto.service/auto-service-annotations/index.json:9:    "description" : "AutoService Annotations provides the @AutoService annotation used to mark Java service-provider implementations for ServiceLoader registration. It is the compile-time annotation artifact used with the AutoService annotation processor, which generates META-INF/services provider-configuration files.",
metadata/org.jline/jline-reader/index.json:10:    "description" : "JLine Reader provides the line-editing, history, completion, key binding, and prompt-reading APIs used to build interactive command-line interfaces on the JVM. It sits on top of JLine terminal abstractions so Java applications can implement shell-like input behavior across supported consoles and terminal backends.",
metadata/org.jline/jline-reader/index.json:51:    "description" : "JLine Reader provides the line-editing, history, completion, key binding, and prompt-reading APIs used to build interactive command-line interfaces on the JVM. It sits on top of JLine terminal abstractions so Java applications can implement shell-like input behavior across supported consoles and terminal backends.",
metadata/org.scalameta/mdoc-parser_2.13/index.json:9:    "description" : "mdoc-parser is the parser module for mdoc, a Scala documentation tool that processes typechecked Markdown. It parses Markdown text into structured text and code-fence parts so mdoc can identify, render, and transform Scala code blocks.",
metadata/org.scalameta/mdoc-parser_2.13/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-impl/index.json:9:    "description" : "JJWT is a Java library for creating, parsing, and validating JSON Web Tokens on the JVM and Android. The jjwt-impl artifact provides the internal runtime implementation behind the public jjwt-api interfaces, including builders, parsers, signature algorithms, and compression support.",
metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-impl/index.json:31:    "description" : "JJWT is a Java library for creating, parsing, and validating JSON Web Tokens on the JVM and Android. The jjwt-impl artifact provides the runtime implementation behind the public jjwt-api interfaces, including JWT builders, parsers, signature handling, and compression support.",
metadata/org.jline/jline/index.json:13:    "description": "JLine is a Java library for building interactive command-line applications with terminal abstraction, line editing, history, and completion support. The jline bundle packages the core JLine modules, including terminal, reader, builtins, console, style, and remote shell components.",
metadata/org.scalameta/scalafmt-config_2.13/index.json:9:    "description" : "Scalafmt config is the Scalafmt module that parses and represents formatting configuration files. It provides JVM classes used by Scalafmt components to read HOCON-based .scalafmt.conf settings and turn them into typed configuration data.",
metadata/org.scalameta/scalafmt-config_2.13/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/index.json:10:    "description" : "jjwt-jackson provides Jackson-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementations for JJWT. It lets JJWT encode JWT headers and claims to JSON and parse them back using Jackson.",
metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/index.json:25:    "description" : "jjwt-jackson provides Jackson-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementations for JJWT. It lets JJWT encode JWT headers and claims to JSON and parse them back using Jackson.",
metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/index.json:45:    "description" : "jjwt-jackson provides Jackson-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementations for JJWT. It lets JJWT encode JWT headers and claims to JSON and parse them back using Jackson.",
metadata/org.jline/jline-native/index.json:9:    "description" : "JLine Native Library packages JNI bindings and platform-specific native binaries used by JLine to access low-level terminal functionality. It provides Java APIs and native resources for POSIX and Windows console operations, including metadata needed when the library is used in GraalVM Native Image builds.",
metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-gson/index.json:9:    "description" : "Provides Gson-based JSON serialization and deserialization support for the JJWT library. When present on the runtime classpath, it lets JJWT automatically use Gson to process JWT headers and claims.",
metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-gson/index.json:29:    "description" : "Provides Gson-based JSON serialization and deserialization support for the JJWT library. When present on the runtime classpath, it lets JJWT automatically use Gson to process JWT headers and claims.",
metadata/org.scalameta/munit_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "MUnit is a Scala testing framework that provides suites, assertions, fixtures, and test discovery through JUnit-compatible runners. The Scala 3 artifact publishes the core JVM test framework for Scala 3 projects, letting build tools run synchronous and asynchronous Scala tests with useful diffing and failure reporting.",
metadata/org.scalameta/munit_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.scalameta/munit-diff_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "MUnit Diff provides Scala diffing utilities used by MUnit to compare values and render actionable assertion failures. The Scala 3 JVM artifact includes unified diff algorithms, patch data structures, equality helpers, and console printers for producing readable test failure output.",
metadata/org.scalameta/munit-diff_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.scalameta/junit-interface/index.json:9:    "description" : "junit-interface is a Java implementation of sbt's test interface for running JUnit 4 tests. It lets build tools and test runners discover JUnit test fingerprints, apply filters, execute test tasks, and report results through the sbt test-interface API.",
metadata/org.scalameta/scalafmt-core_2.13/index.json:9:    "description" : "Scalafmt Core implements the core formatting engine for Scalafmt, the Scala code formatter. It parses Scala source, applies Scalafmt configuration and rewrite rules, and produces consistently formatted Scala code for use by the CLI, build-tool integrations, and other JVM callers.",
