metadata/org.http4s/http4s-dsl_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "http4s DSL provides a concise Scala syntax for defining http4s HTTP routes, requests, responses, matchers, and extractors. It builds on http4s core to make functional HTTP services easier to express with pattern matching and composable route definitions.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-dsl_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.objenesis/objenesis/index.json:9:    "description" : "Objenesis is a Java library for instantiating objects without invoking their constructors. It is commonly used by serialization, proxying, and mocking frameworks that need to create objects beyond standard reflection.",
metadata/org.scalameta/scalameta_2.13/index.json:9:    "description" : "Scalameta provides Scala metaprogramming APIs for parsing, tokenizing, and representing Scala source code as syntax trees. The scalameta_2.13 artifact is the Scala 2.13 JVM umbrella module that brings together its public APIs, including parsers, trees, tokens, quasiquotes, and related utilities.",
metadata/org.scalameta/scalameta_2.13/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/javax.servlet.jsp/jsp-api/index.json:9:    "description" : "This artifact provides the JavaServer Pages 2.1 API contracts, including core JSP, tag extension, and expression language interfaces used by JSP containers and applications. It defines standard types that JSP engines and custom tag libraries implement at compile time and runtime.",
metadata/org.apache.tomcat/tomcat-jdbc/index.json:71:    "description" : "Tomcat JDBC is Apache Tomcat's JDBC connection pool implementation for creating, managing, and monitoring pooled database connections. It provides a DataSource API with pooling, validation, JMX integration, and interceptors for Java applications running inside or outside Tomcat.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-core_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "http4s-core_3 provides the core Scala 3 HTTP model and abstractions for building functional HTTP clients and servers, including requests, responses, headers, routes, entities, and related syntax. It is the foundation used by http4s client and server modules while integrating with Cats Effect and FS2 for effectful and streaming HTTP programs.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-core_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/com.android.tools.jack/jack-api/index.json:9:    "description" : "Jack API provides Java interfaces for discovering and configuring Jack compiler providers at runtime. It exposes versioned compilation configuration, task creation, reporting, multidex, collision-policy, and source-version options used by tools that invoke Jack.",
metadata/org.apache.tomcat/tomcat-juli/index.json:9:    "description" : "Apache Tomcat JULI is Tomcat's packaged logging implementation built on java.util.logging and a renamed fork of Apache Commons Logging. It provides a container-friendly LogManager, handlers, formatters, and per-classloader configuration so Tomcat and web applications can keep logging isolated.",
metadata/org.apache.tomcat/tomcat-juli/index.json:42:    "description" : "Apache Tomcat JULI is Tomcat's packaged logging implementation built around java.util.logging and a renamed Commons Logging API. It provides class-loader-aware log management, handlers, and formatters so Tomcat and web applications can keep logging configuration and output separated.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-ember-server_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "http4s Ember Server is the Ember backend implementation for running http4s servers on the JVM. It provides a lightweight, functional HTTP server for the http4s ecosystem using cats-effect and FS2.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-ember-server_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.apache.tomcat/tomcat-annotations-api/index.json:9:    "description" : "Apache Tomcat Annotations API provides the Jakarta Annotations API classes distributed by the Tomcat project. It supplies common annotations for lifecycle callbacks, resource injection, security constraints, and data source definitions without requiring the full Tomcat server.",
metadata/org.scala-lang.modules/scala-parser-combinators_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "scala-parser-combinators provides Scala's standard parser combinator APIs for building recursive-descent parsers from composable parser values. It is distributed as a separate Scala module for projects that need parser combinators, with support for parsing token streams, regular-expression input, packrat parsing, and position-aware input.",
metadata/org.scala-lang.modules/scala-parser-combinators_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-server_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "http4s-server_3 provides the core Scala 3 server APIs for http4s, including routes, routing composition, server builders, middleware, WebSocket support, and static content helpers. It is used to build functional HTTP services on the JVM with Cats Effect and FS2, while backend modules provide concrete runtime servers.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-server_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.apache.tomcat/annotations-api/index.json:9:    "description" : "Apache Tomcat Annotations API is the Tomcat 6 distribution of common Java EE annotation classes, including lifecycle, resource, security, EJB, JPA, and web-service reference annotations. It lets applications compile against those annotation APIs without depending on the full Tomcat server.",
metadata/dev.zio/zio-http_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "ZIO HTTP is a Scala library for building HTTP server and client applications on top of ZIO and Netty. It provides typed, composable APIs for routing, endpoints, middleware, WebSockets, streaming, templating, OpenAPI integration, and test support.",
metadata/dev.zio/zio-http_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-core/index.json:8:    "description" : "Google Cloud Core provides shared foundational types and utilities used by Google Cloud Java client libraries, including service options, retry helpers, paging, IAM policy models, timestamps, and testing support. It supplies common abstractions for credentials, transport configuration, service RPC factories, and base service behavior so individual Google Cloud clients can share consistent runtime infrastructure.",
metadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-core/index.json:23:    "description" : "Google Cloud Core provides shared abstractions and base types used by Google Cloud Java client libraries. It includes service options, retry helpers, paging, IAM policy, resource metadata, and other common infrastructure for building and using Google Cloud service clients.",
metadata/org.glassfish.jaxb/txw2/index.json:9:    "description" : "TXW2 is a typed XML writer library that lets Java code generate XML documents through annotated writer interfaces. It provides runtime support for building structured XML output with SAX, StAX, DOM, and stream-based serializers.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-ember-core_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "http4s Ember Core provides the shared protocol, parsing, encoding, error, and HTTP/2 support used by the Ember client and server backends in the http4s Scala HTTP stack. It supplies the low-level building blocks that turn bytes into http4s requests and responses and support functional, streaming HTTP programs built on Cats Effect and FS2.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-ember-core_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-pubsub/index.json:9:    "description" : "Google Cloud Pub/Sub is the Java client library for publishing messages to and subscribing from Google Cloud Pub/Sub topics and subscriptions. It provides high-level publisher, subscriber, admin, streaming pull, and schema service clients built on Google Cloud's generated API stack.",
metadata/com.intellij/annotations/index.json:9:    "description" : "IntelliJ IDEA Annotations provides annotation types such as @NotNull, @Nullable, and @Language for documenting code contracts and guiding IDE inspections. It is a small Java annotation library used to express nullability, localization, formatting, and other static-analysis hints without adding runtime framework behavior.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-circe_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "http4s-circe integrates the http4s HTTP toolkit with Circe JSON by providing entity encoders and decoders for JSON values and codecs. It lets Scala applications read and write JSON request and response bodies using Circe in http4s clients and servers.",
metadata/org.http4s/http4s-circe_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-jpamodelgen/index.json:9:    "description" : "Hibernate JPAMetaModelGen is an annotation processor that generates JPA static metamodel classes from annotated entity classes. It supports type-safe Criteria API queries by producing canonical model classes during Java compilation.",
metadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-monitoring/index.json:9:    "description" : "Google Cloud Monitoring is the Java client library for the Cloud Monitoring API. It lets JVM applications create and query metrics, monitored resources, alerting policies, uptime checks, and other monitoring data through generated gRPC and HTTP clients.",
metadata/org.atteo.classindex/classindex/index.json:9:    "description" : "ClassIndex is a Java annotation processor and runtime API that builds indexes of annotated classes, subclasses, implementors, and package classes at compile time. Applications can query those generated indexes at runtime to avoid slower classpath scanning while remaining compatible with standard Java mechanisms such as ServiceLoader.",
metadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-firestore/index.json:9:    "description" : "Google Cloud Firestore is the Java idiomatic client library for Cloud Firestore. It lets JVM applications access Firestore's NoSQL document database using Google Cloud's client APIs and gRPC transport.",
metadata/org.iq80.snappy/snappy/index.json:9:    "description" : "Snappy is a pure Java port of Google's Snappy compression library. It provides APIs and stream classes for compressing and decompressing data in Snappy block and framed formats.",
metadata/org.iq80.snappy/snappy/index.json:23:    "description" : "Snappy is a pure Java port of Google's Snappy compression library. It provides APIs and stream classes for compressing and decompressing data in Snappy block and framed formats.",
metadata/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/index.json:9:    "description" : "Jersey Guava is Jersey's repackaged and shaded copy of Google Guava, relocating Guava classes under the jersey.repackaged namespace. It supplies common collections, caching, concurrency, primitives, and utility APIs used internally by Jersey while avoiding dependency conflicts with application-provided Guava versions.",
metadata/jakarta.annotation/jakarta.annotation-api/index.json:9:    "description" : "Jakarta Annotations defines standard Java annotations for common semantic concepts used across Jakarta EE and related Java technologies. This artifact provides the version 3.0.0 API types in the jakarta.annotation package, including lifecycle, security, resource, nullability, priority, and generated-code annotations.",
metadata/jakarta.annotation/jakarta.annotation-api/index.json:23:    "description" : "Jakarta Annotations defines standard Java annotations for common semantic concepts used across Jakarta EE and related Java technologies. This artifact provides the version 2.1.0 API types in the jakarta.annotation package, including lifecycle, security, resource, and generated-code annotations.",
metadata/jakarta.annotation/jakarta.annotation-api/index.json:38:    "description" : "Jakarta Annotations defines standard Java annotations for common semantic concepts used across Jakarta EE and other Java technologies. This artifact provides the version 2.0.0 API types in the `jakarta.annotation` package, including lifecycle, security, resource, and generated-code annotations.",
metadata/jakarta.annotation/jakarta.annotation-api/index.json:52:    "description" : "Jakarta Annotations defines a standard set of common Java annotations that support declarative programming across Java technologies. This artifact provides the 1.3.3 API types in the `javax.annotation` package, including lifecycle, resource, and generated-code annotations.",
metadata/com.google.cloud/proto-google-cloud-firestore-bundle-v1/index.json:9:    "description" : "This artifact provides generated Java Protocol Buffer classes and proto definitions for Google Cloud Firestore bundle messages. It models bundle metadata, named queries, bundled queries, and bundled document metadata used when serializing or consuming Firestore bundle data.",
metadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-logging/index.json:9:    "description": "Google Cloud Logging is the Java idiomatic client library for the Google Cloud Logging API. It lets JVM applications write, query, and manage log entries, metrics, sinks, and related logging resources in Google Cloud.",
metadata/commons-lang/commons-lang/index.json:9:    "description" : "Apache Commons Lang provides reusable Java utility classes that supplement the core java.lang API with helpers for strings, numbers, objects, reflection, dates, and system values. It helps applications avoid reimplementing common low-level programming tasks by packaging widely used language-level utilities for Java.",
metadata/commons-lang/commons-lang/index.json:23:    "description" : "Apache Commons Lang provides Java utility classes that extend core language functionality for strings, numbers, objects, system properties, serialization, exceptions, and builder-style helpers. Version 1.0 is a JVM library packaged as a JAR for use by Java applications.",
metadata/org.jboss.spec.javax.transaction/jboss-transaction-api_1.2_spec/index.json:9:    "description" : "This library provides the Java Transaction API 1.2 interfaces and annotations under javax.transaction for application-managed and container-managed transaction coordination. It supplies the standard exception types and contracts such as UserTransaction, TransactionManager, Transaction, Transactional, and TransactionSynchronizationRegistry used by Java EE runtimes and applications.",
metadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-core-grpc/index.json:9:    "description" : "google-cloud-core-grpc provides shared gRPC transport infrastructure for Google Cloud Java client libraries. It includes transport options, shared resource management, and base exception handling used by gRPC-based Google Cloud clients.",
metadata/redis.clients/jedis/index.json:9:    "description" : "Jedis is a Java client library for Redis that provides synchronous APIs for commands, pooling, transactions, pipelining, and Redis cluster usage. It lets Java applications communicate with Redis servers while exposing Redis data structures and operations through a compact client interface.",
metadata/redis.clients/jedis/index.json:31:    "description" : "Jedis is a Java client library for Redis that provides synchronous APIs for commands, pooling, transactions, pipelining, and Redis cluster usage. It lets Java applications communicate with Redis servers while exposing Redis data structures and operations through a compact client interface.",
metadata/redis.clients/jedis/index.json:45:    "description" : "Jedis is a Java client library for Redis that provides synchronous APIs for commands, pooling, transactions, pipelining, and Redis cluster usage. It lets Java applications communicate with Redis servers while exposing Redis data structures and operations through a compact client interface.",
metadata/redis.clients/jedis/index.json:59:    "description" : "Jedis is a Java client library for Redis that provides synchronous APIs for commands, pooling, transactions, pipelining, and Redis cluster usage. It lets Java applications communicate with Redis servers while exposing Redis data structures and operations through a compact client interface.",
metadata/redis.clients/jedis/index.json:83:    "description" : "Jedis is a Java client library for Redis that provides synchronous APIs for commands, pooling, transactions, pipelining, and Redis cluster usage. It lets Java applications communicate with Redis servers while exposing Redis data structures and operations through a compact client interface.",
metadata/redis.clients/jedis/index.json:105:    "description" : "Jedis is a Java client library for Redis that provides synchronous APIs for commands, pooling, transactions, pipelining, and Redis cluster usage. It lets Java applications communicate with Redis servers while exposing Redis data structures and operations through a compact client interface.",
metadata/redis.clients/jedis/index.json:128:    "description" : "Jedis is a Java client library for Redis that provides synchronous APIs for commands, pooling, transactions, pipelining, and Redis cluster usage. It lets Java applications communicate with Redis servers while exposing Redis data structures and operations through a compact client interface.",
metadata/org.checkerframework/checker-qual/index.json:8:    "description" : "checker-qual packages the Checker Framework's type qualifier annotations and supporting classes for Java. Developers use these annotations to express program properties that the Checker Framework can verify during type checking.",
metadata/org.checkerframework/checker-qual/index.json:23:    "description" : "checker-qual packages the Checker Framework's type qualifier annotations for Java. Developers use these annotations to specify code properties that can be verified by the Checker Framework's pluggable type-checkers.",
metadata/commons-daemon/commons-daemon/index.json:9:    "description" : "Apache Commons Daemon provides APIs and native launchers for running Java applications with daemon-style lifecycle control. It supports Unix service execution through jsvc and Windows service execution through procrun.",
metadata/org.jboss.arquillian.core/arquillian-core-impl-base/index.json:9:    "description" : "Arquillian Core Implementation Base provides the base runtime implementation for Arquillian Core. It implements the manager, event, injection, context, threading, and extension-loading services used by Arquillian components.",
metadata/org.jboss.arquillian.core/arquillian-core-impl-base/index.json:40:    "description" : "Arquillian Core Implementation Base provides the base runtime implementation for Arquillian Core. It implements the manager, event, injection, context, threading, and extension-loading services used by Arquillian components.",
metadata/org.scala-lang.modules/scala-java8-compat_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "scala-java8-compat is a Scala compatibility library that bridges Scala APIs with Java 8 functional, collection, concurrency, duration, and optional types. It provides adapters and extension methods for converting between Scala functions, collections, Future/Promise, Option, and Java 8 interfaces such as java.util.function, Streams, CompletionStage, Duration, and Optional.",
metadata/org.scala-lang.modules/scala-java8-compat_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/com.typesafe.scala-logging/scala-logging_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "Scala Logging is an idiomatic Scala facade around SLF4J that provides convenient logger wrappers, lazy and strict logging traits, and contextual logging helpers. It uses Scala macros to preserve efficient level checks while letting Scala code write concise interpolated log messages.",
metadata/com.typesafe.scala-logging/scala-logging_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.jboss.arquillian.core/arquillian-core-spi/index.json:9:    "description" : "Arquillian Core SPI provides service-provider interfaces and extension hooks for the Arquillian core runtime. It defines contracts for contexts, event processing, object stores, extension loading, manager creation, and observer invocation used by Arquillian integrations and extensions.",
metadata/org.apache.pdfbox/pdfbox/index.json:9:    "description" : "Apache PDFBox is an open source Java library for creating, parsing, rendering, printing, and manipulating PDF documents. It also provides content extraction capabilities and command-line tools for common PDF workflows.",
metadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/index.json:20:    "description": "Hibernate Core is the main module of Hibernate ORM, providing object-relational mapping between Java domain models and relational databases. It implements Jakarta Persistence and adds native APIs for mapping, querying, caching, and managing persistence.",
metadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/index.json:44:    "description": "Hibernate Core is the main module of Hibernate ORM, providing object-relational mapping between Java domain models and relational databases. It implements JPA and adds native APIs for mapping, querying, caching, and managing persistence.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/geny_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "Geny is a small Scala library that provides push-based versions of common standard library interfaces, centered on Generator as an inverse of Iterator and Writable and Readable for byte and text IO. It helps model lazy streaming data with deterministic cleanup and lightweight interoperation with standard Scala collections and Java IO types.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/geny_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-spatial/index.json:13:    "description": "Hibernate Spatial integrates Spatial/GIS data support into Hibernate ORM. It lets Hibernate map and query geospatial types and functions through supported spatial databases.",
metadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-spatial/index.json:31:    "description": "Hibernate Spatial integrates Spatial/GIS data support into Hibernate ORM. It lets Hibernate map and query geospatial types and functions through supported spatial databases.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/fansi_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "Fansi is a Scala library for representing, parsing, and rendering strings with ANSI terminal styling such as colors, backgrounds, bold, underline, and reverse video. It provides immutable fansi.Str values and formatting attributes so command-line applications can measure, concatenate, split, overlay, and safely render colored text without manually managing escape sequences.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/fansi_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/javax.inject/javax.inject/index.json:9:    "description" : "javax.inject provides the standard JSR-330 dependency injection annotations and Provider interface for Java. It defines portable injection contracts such as @Inject, @Named, @Qualifier, @Scope, and @Singleton for use by dependency injection frameworks.",
metadata/org.ow2.asm/asm-debug-all/index.json:9:    "description" : "ASM Debug All is the all-in-one debug build of ASM 5.0.1, a Java bytecode manipulation framework for reading, writing, and transforming class files. It bundles the ASM core, tree, commons, util, analysis, XML, and related debug-enabled components so tools can inspect, trace, analyze, and generate Java bytecode from one artifact.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/upack_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "uPack is the MessagePack component of uPickle, providing an in-memory MessagePack data model plus readers and writers for parsing and serializing MessagePack bytes. It is published for Scala 3 and integrates with uPickle's visitor-based serialization infrastructure.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/upack_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.ow2.asm/asm-commons/index.json:9:    "description" : "ASM Commons provides reusable adapters and helper classes for ASM's Java bytecode manipulation framework. It includes remappers, advice and generator adapters, local variable utilities, and other components that simplify transforming and analyzing compiled Java class files.",
metadata/org.thymeleaf.extras/thymeleaf-extras-springsecurity6/index.json:9:    "description" : "Thymeleaf Extras Spring Security 6 integrates Thymeleaf templates with Spring Security 6 by adding the SpringSecurityDialect and security expression utility objects. It lets views access authentication details and conditionally render content based on authorization expressions, URLs, and ACL permissions.",
metadata/io.javaslang/javaslang/index.json:9:    "description" : "Javaslang is a functional programming library for Java 8 that extends the standard library with persistent collections, tuples, functions, pattern matching support, and control types such as Option, Either, Try, and Validation. It helps Java applications model immutable data, transformations, and functional error handling with APIs designed for ordinary JVM use.",
metadata/org.ow2.asm/asm-tree/index.json:9:    "description" : "ASM Tree provides an object-model API for reading, generating, and transforming Java bytecode as mutable class, method, and instruction nodes. It is part of the ASM framework and is useful when bytecode transformations need random access to class structure instead of ASM's streaming visitor API.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/fastparse_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "FastParse is a Scala parser-combinator library for building efficient parsers for structured text such as programming languages, data formats, and domain-specific languages. It provides composable parsing primitives, error reporting, and cross-platform support that let applications define readable parsers directly in Scala code.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/fastparse_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.hibernate.validator/hibernate-validator/index.json:13:    "description": "Hibernate Validator is the reference implementation of Jakarta Bean Validation and provides annotation-based and programmatic constraint validation for Java applications. It validates beans, method parameters, and return values and includes support for custom constraints and message interpolation.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/upickle-implicits_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "uPickle is a Scala JSON and MessagePack serialization library for reading and writing structured data. The upickle-implicits module supplies macro and implicit derivation of readers and writers for Scala data types, including case classes, enums, tuples, and collections.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/upickle-implicits_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/io.javaslang/javaslang-match/index.json:9:    "description" : "Javaslang Match provides annotations and an annotation processor that generate support code for structural pattern matching in Java. It is part of the Javaslang functional programming library and helps Java applications express match-style control flow with generated pattern helpers.",
metadata/org.ow2.asm/asm-analysis/index.json:9:    "description" : "ASM Analysis provides the static analysis API for ASM's Java bytecode manipulation framework. It supplies analyzers, interpreters, frames, and value abstractions that help inspect and verify method bytecode.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/scalatags_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "Scalatags is a Scala library for constructing HTML, XML, and SVG fragments with a type-safe Scala DSL. The JVM artifact can render markup as text from Scala 3 code, making it useful for server-side HTML generation and shared markup definitions.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/scalatags_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/com.lihaoyi/pprint_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "PPrint is a Scala pretty-printing library for rendering values and types as readable text with configurable width, indentation, colors, and truncation. It helps Scala applications inspect data structures and type shapes in logs, consoles, and debugging output without hand-written formatting logic.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/pprint_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.ow2.asm/asm/index.json:8:    "description" : "ASM is a small and fast Java bytecode manipulation framework for reading, writing, and transforming Java class files. The core asm artifact provides the event-based visitor API used to generate bytecode, inspect classes, and implement tools such as compilers, profilers, and code generators.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/sourcecode_2.13/index.json:9:    "description" : "SourceCode is a small Scala library that supplies compile-time source context such as file names, line numbers, enclosing names, argument text, and packages as values or implicits. It uses Scala macros instead of runtime reflection or stack inspection, making the captured context useful for diagnostics, logging, debugging, and DSL error reporting.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/sourcecode_2.13/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/com.lihaoyi/requests_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "Requests-Scala is a Scala HTTP client inspired by Python Requests for making synchronous HTTP calls from JVM applications. It wraps Java networking APIs with a small Scala interface for building requests, sending request bodies, handling headers and authentication, and reading responses.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/requests_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/org.ow2.asm/asm-util/index.json:9:    "description" : "ASM Util provides utility classes and command-line-oriented tools for ASM's Java bytecode manipulation framework, including bytecode checking, tracing, textification, and ASMifier generation. It helps developers inspect compiled classes and generate ASM visitor code that reproduces equivalent bytecode structures.",
metadata/org.rxtx/rxtx/index.json:9:    "description" : "RXTX provides Java APIs and native bindings for serial and parallel port communication through the gnu.io package. It lets JVM applications discover ports, open them, and exchange data with attached hardware using platform-specific native libraries.",
metadata/org.apache.pdfbox/pdfbox-io/index.json:9:    "description" : "Apache PDFBox is an open source Java library for reading, writing, and manipulating PDF documents. The pdfbox-io artifact provides the IO utilities and random-access stream/cache classes used by PDFBox.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/fansi_2.13/index.json:9:    "description" : "Fansi is a Scala library for constructing, parsing, and manipulating ANSI-colored strings in command-line programs. It wraps text in typed attributes so code can measure visible length, concatenate styled segments, apply overlays, split strings, and render escape sequences without leaking or corrupting terminal colors.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/fansi_2.13/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/com.lihaoyi/os-zip/index.json:9:    "description" : "os-zip packages os-lib's shaded ZIP implementation, providing Java classes for reading, writing, and manipulating ZIP entries with support for encodings, extra fields, permissions, and Zip64 data. It is used by os-lib's file-system APIs when creating and extracting archives while preserving ZIP metadata that java.util.zip does not fully model.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/upickle-core_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "uPickle Core is the shared Scala 3 runtime layer for uPickle, providing core visitor, parser, renderer, buffering, and transformation abstractions used by uPickle's JSON and MessagePack serializers. It supplies low-level data model traversal and streaming utilities that higher-level uPickle, ujson, and upack modules build on for reading and writing structured data.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/upickle-core_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/com.lihaoyi/ujson_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "ujson is the JSON AST and parser/rendering component of uPickle, a Scala JSON and MessagePack serialization library. It provides Scala data types and APIs for reading, transforming, and writing JSON values, published here as a Scala 3 JVM artifact.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/ujson_3/index.json:10:    "language" : {
metadata/com.lihaoyi/ujson_3/index.json:30:    "description" : "ujson is the JSON AST and parser/rendering component of uPickle, a Scala JSON and MessagePack serialization library. It provides Scala data types and APIs for reading, transforming, and writing JSON values, published here as a Scala 3 JVM artifact.",
metadata/com.lihaoyi/ujson_3/index.json:31:    "language" : {
metadata/javax.interceptor/javax.interceptor-api/index.json:9:    "description" : "This library defines the Java Interceptors API in the `javax.interceptor` package, including interceptor bindings, interceptor declarations, and the invocation context contract. It is used by Java EE containers and compatible frameworks to apply cross-cutting behavior such as lifecycle, method, and timeout interception around application code.",
