metadata/io.kotest/kotest-common-jvm/index.json:9:    "description" : "kotest-common-jvm is the JVM variant of Kotest's common support module, providing shared annotations, platform utilities, environment access, reflection helpers, stack trace handling, timeout helpers, and test-name coroutine context support. It is used by Kotest's Kotlin testing framework as low-level infrastructure for JVM tests rather than as a standalone test runner or assertion API.",
